            <div type="edition" xml:space="preserve"><head>Text</head><ab><lb n="1"/>
                <expan><abbr>D</abbr><ex>is</ex></expan> <expan><abbr>M</abbr><ex>anibus</ex></expan> <lb n="2"/>Curo Pe<lb break="no" n="3"/>tilli Seve<lb break="no" n="4"/>ri <expan><abbr>ser</abbr><ex>vo</ex></expan> <expan><abbr>v</abbr><ex>ixit</ex></expan> <expan><abbr>p</abbr><ex>ius</ex></expan> <lb n="5"/><expan><abbr>an</abbr><ex>nos</ex></expan> XVIIII <lb n="6"/><expan><abbr>Homul</abbr><ex>la</ex></expan> <expan><abbr>con</abbr><ex>iugi</ex></expan>
            </ab></div>
            <div type="commentary">
                <p>Das 1. L in Petillius hat die Form eines griechischen Lambda. Das 2. scheint verschrieben. (B): Z. 2/3: Petilui statt Petilli; Z. 6: Homul(ia) statt Homul(la). (C): Unzutreffende Ausführungen zu Curus. Unten links: von anderer Hand P eingemeißelt, gehört nicht zur Inschrift. Material: rosa Kalkstein.</p>
            </div>
